b'The future of retail is local; it is also data-driven, flexible, specialized.  @faire_wholesale is here to power this evolution.  5/'

b'This group has operated with flexibly to meet the moment and the needs of their communities and in turn some 90% of consumers are planning to commit their spending power to local businesses this holiday season. 2/'

b'Our investment is based on a long term outlook, but in the immediate moment digital music/comedy/events can bring much needed joy &  distraction after months of isolation \xe2\x80\x94 @moment_house  occupies a bright spot for creators and audiences. 7/'

b'Co-founders @arjunmehta_ & @shraybans bring an artful eye to their technology savvy, having conceived and brought to life a stand out product experience.  They have already forged meaningful inroads with music industry execs and talent. 6/'

b'We see a new category emerging, propelled by 3 tailwinds: (1) consumer willingness to pay for experiences & services > goods, (2) advanced digital connectivity & design evolution, (3) a growing movement of performers engaging with fans directly via owned social channels. 5/'
b'So now this: @Moment_House a self-service digital events platform for creators that has built a beautifully designed, interactive, and ticketed new unit of content called a *Moment*. 4/'

b'Digital events are typically cast on free platforms & are often low-fi, generic, uninspiring. Because these are free ad-based platforms, the content has been commoditized and lacks a premium or unique experience that consumers will pay for. 3/'

b'The concert/event industry ($35B U.S. mrkt) & live streaming industry ($24B U.S.) have grown tremendously over the past decade - proven recently by 12M viewers of Travis Scott\xe2\x80\x99s Fornite experience - yet artists struggle to monetize digital events & create engaging experiences. 2/'

b'Digital events don\xe2\x80\x99t need to replace live in person \xe2\x80\x94 done right they should stand on their own, offering another way to engage and experience. Enter @moment_house \nhttps://t.co/XjzYpwj6K8 1/'

b"We at @forerunnerVC are motivated by and eager to support @join_real 's potential to drive meaningful positive change for people in need and those who value the lifelong pursuit of wellbeing.  8/."

b'Real accomplishes this with 3 tiers of service: asynchronous therapy pathways, group therapy, 1:1 care. By bringing together a flow of habit-forming services augmented by tech, Real champions an affordable option that celebrates, rather than simply normalizes, mental health. 7/'

b'Founder @arielasafira captured our imagination with her reimagined model for delivering therapy using empathy, design & progressive care. She, as do I, believes that mental health should be an ongoing practice & more reflective of a lifestyle than an acute point solution. 6/'
b'Until @join_real\xe2\x80\x94 a better, modern alternative that stands to address the need while seeing today\xe2\x80\x99s patient for what they are willing and comfortable to embrace. 5/'

b'This means therapy becomes generally hard to access and a very expensive solution. To compound the issue, over 60% of therapists will not or cannot accept health insurance, leaving patients to bear the cost. 4/'

b'While demand is high, there is a severe shortage of providers. In the US, there is 1 mental health provider for every 529 people who need help. Among child/adolescent psychiatrists the gap is wider: >15M patients are in need, yet only ~ 8k such psychiatrists are practicing. 3/'

b'Nearly 1/5th of adults suffer from serious psychological distress, while fear and stigma too often keep us from talking openly about challenges. The 2 most common solutions for mental distress are medication & therapy. 2/'

b'The COVID-19 crisis has only further expedited the need for mental health solutions, and cultural shifts have made it even more apparent that we must change both the format and the access of therapy.  Therapy reimagined at @join_real launches today. https://t.co/GDLmkSYvmD . 1/'
